args:
The traitor who implanted false memories in
Pinon while plotting to revive a demon is
Basileus. Pinon resolves to defeat her mentor.
However, a demon in the form of Gabriel
manifests out of the miasma leaking from
the sealing stone, and attacks the party.
Miasma spills forth from the sealing\nstone without cease! I have accumulated\nenough memories to release the seal!
Why, Basileus. I must say,\nI am ever so grateful to you.
Thanks to this stone you gave me, I can\nstand amidst the shoulders of gods.\nNay, I have ascended to divinity myself!
You grasp power, that much is true.\nWhat you will become, however, is\nnot a god, but a demon.
Through miasma it shall be incarnated.\nIt seems it will take some time until it is\nfully manifested.
Ah, Faris. I must applaud your deductive\nreasoning. And yet you've made one error.
Madame did not lend me a sealing stone.\nShe was returning it.
You gave her the sealing stone?
Madame is nothing more than a pawn\nthat I selected from the Church's arrestees.
Madame's role was to collect the\nmemories needed to unlock the seal.\nParadise is a cover to deceive the people.
How roundabout. I'd think it would be\nmore efficient to just disperse the miasma\nlike in the wroth incident.
Going large-scale and attracting the\nChurch's notice at an early stage would\nonly hinder the plan.
The more of the requisite memories to\nrelease the seal one accumulates, the\nstronger the resultant demon.

Still, word of Paradise found its way to
Church ears. Thus did they order an
undercover investigation to be carried
out by the apostles.
And so in order to guide the investigation\nthe way you wanted, you took Little Pi's\nmemories—

—and rewrote them, yes. Though that
particular scheme failed because you
suggested that the investigation continue,
{player_name}.
So you were keeping an eye on us while\nwe were in town?
I've been here since early this morning\nunder orders to ensure that the demon\nmanifests properly.
I had no intention of revealing myself,\neven after you decided to continue the\ninvestigation. But—
I see. So this man was meeting in secret\nwith Madame.
Aren't YOU a little busybody, asking all\nthese super-specific details about her man!
In any case, thank you for the information.
Oh! You're the one who was with\nMadame...
You saw my face, did you? Evidently,\nI ought to have been more stringent\nuntil the deed was fully done.
Faris is onto me, then.\nFortunately, he now operates alone.
The false memories I implanted into Pinon\nhave taken root, and now the seed of\ndoubt sprouts around Faris.
Very well. I shall make use of it all,\nalong with the death of this girl.

Then you erected the barrier that
inhibits the telepathic communications
between angels, and approached us
when we had fled into the mountains...
Rescuing you from the Templars was all\npart of the plan. I arranged for Madame\nto send them after you.

I did it all to give the impression that I was
your ally. Particularly in your case,
{player_name}, as this was to be
our first meeting.
You even fed us false information and tried\nto get us to help you take down Faris...

You could've skipped all of that.
With the stone in your possession
again, you could have implanted
fake memories in me as well.

You are ever wise, Faris. Had I done such
a thing, you would've picked up on small
inconsistencies and realized that your
memories had been manipulated.
Thus, I had to kill you. After that, I would\nmake a falsified report to Regina, and\ncover up any inconvenient facts.
But then the coward Ryszarda confronted\nme—an unexpected twist that gave you an\nopening to hurl sanctified water at Pinon.
In the end, the only one who lived\nup to my expectations was you, Pinon.
She looked up to you.\nYou realize that, don't you?

She thought you were the very model of
what an apostle ought to be. I can't believe
you would run roughshod all over her
feelings!
Your ＂daughter＂ was blinded by what\nshe wanted to see. Nothing more.
Basileus, tell me something: How long\nhave you been working against the\nChurch—against us?
My heart has never been with the Church,\nnot since the very beginning.
What about that smile you gave the\nkidnapped boy? Was that all just an act?
All my behavior has always been\nno more than a guise I was obliged\nto adopt in order to mask my true feelings.
I see... Thank you for telling me that.\nNow my doubts can bind me no longer.
You are our enemy. I am the apostle\nPinon, and I shall administer Her will!
Found your pluck, have you? Sadly,\nI'm not the one you need to be fighting.
Why do you imagine I have so laboriously\nexplained every last detail of my actions\nto you people?
Yes... I seethe...with POWER!\nThis power... It rivals the GODS!
It's the same as during the wroth incident.\nIt looks just like an angel, but...
With this power, I shall build a true\nparadise. A sweet, mellifluous paradise\nthat bows only to me: MADAME!
Ha ha ha... AHA HA HA HA!\n...Nrgh?! URAAAGH!
Wait. Something's off.\nIt's almost like she's in pain.
I, Madame...\nNO! NOT MADAME!\nIn all my glory, I shall...
Jaldabaoth's consciousness has risen to\nthe surface. This will prove...problematic.
Basileus is running off with the sealing\nstone!
Urgh... The very air is bearing down on us!
I smell it... The stink of sanctified water.\nAre you people with the Church?
What?! I'm getting a completely\ndifferent vibe from before!
You dregs who trapped me in the\nbody of an angel and sealed me in the\notherworld... I will slaughter you all.
Oh, no! The grand hall\nis completely leveled!
Still alive? I'll kill you myself, then.\nI'll kill you over and over again, until\nmy eons of hatred have been SLAKED!
I want to go after Basileus, but I don't\nthink that's in the cards for us at present.
Die... DIE, SCUM OF THE CHURCH!
Weapons at the ready, everyone!\nHere it comes!
